comments.text:
We have a daily job that runs, to dump any audit records associated with creation of any Inbox rules or SMTP forwards. Just run the following Powershell:
    Search-UnifiedAuditLog -EndDate (get-date) -StartDate (get-date).AddDays(-1) -Operations "New-InboxRule","Set-Mailbox" -ResultSize 5000 | `
	Select-Object UserIds,AuditData | `
	Export-Csv forwarded_mail.csv
Then use your favorite text utilities to pull out the relevant log data. I use the following:
cat forwarded_mail.csv | \
	egrep 'InboxRule' | \
	perl -ne '{chomp();
		$rec = $_; 
		my ($src) = $rec =~ m/ClientIP\"\":\"\"(.+?)\"\"/; 
		if ($src =~ m/\[/) {
			# IPv6
			($ip) = $src =~ m/\[(.+)\]/; 
		}
		else {
			# IPv4
			($ip) = $src =~ m/(.+):/; 
		}
		my ($uid) = $rec =~ m/^\"(.+?)\",\"/;
		my ($date) = $rec =~ m/CreationTime\"\":\"\"(.+?)\"\"/;	
		print $ip, "\t", $uid, "\t", $date, "\n"}' | \
	perl /cygdrive/c/analytics/geolocation/wheres-waldo.pl --format=isp >> forwarded_mail.rptecho -e "\n\nSMTP Forward Changes:\n\nIP\t\tAccount\tSMTP Forward\t\tDate/Time (UTC)\tLocation\n" >> forwarded_mail.rptcat forwarded_mail.csv | \
	egrep 'Set-Mailbox' | \
	egrep 'ForwardingSmtpAddress' | \
	perl -ne '{chomp();
		$rec = $_; 
		my ($src) = $rec =~ m/ClientIP\"\":\"\"(.+?)\"\"/; 
		if ($src =~ m/\[/) {
			# IPv6
			($ip) = $src =~ m/\[(.+)\]/; 
		}
		else {
			# IPv4
			($ip) = $src =~ m/(.+):/; 
		}
		my ($uid) = $rec =~ m/^\"(.+?)\",\"/; 
		my ($forward) = $rec =~ m/ForwardingSmtpAddress\"\",\"\"Value\"\":\"\"(.+?)\"/;
		$forward =~ s/smtp://;
		my ($date) = $rec =~ m/CreationTime\"\":\"\"(.+?)\"\"/;	
		print $ip, "\t", $uid, "\t", $forward, "\t", $date, "\n"}' | \
		perl /cygdrive/c/analytics/geolocation/wheres-waldo.pl --format=isp >> forwarded_mail.rpt... then email myself the report.

